social_posts.post_text: Polarized trailer out now for those who missed it! Was such a pleasure making this film with such a talented group of women. Thrilled it is starting to make its way out into the world, beginning with this trailer!

So excited to be nominated for a CSA for my work in Christmas Movie Magic! Such an honor to be recognized amongst super talented folks in the category of Best Lead Performer in a TV Movie.

Thanks to @thecdnacademy for this consideration, and all of the CMM crew - particularly @drewseeley & @tanishathamma for being such fab scene partners, #RobVaughan for bringing us home, and  @slakeyelizabeth for the insane wardrobe that took this character to the next level!

Thanks to @minniestephenson and @channel4news for this piece on @polarized_movie and #queer and #lesbian representation - especially for #palestinians on screen. The movie stars @hollydeveaux and @maxinedenis as two young women in the same small town but very different worlds…

About last night! An honor to be nominated for Best Lead Performer in a TV Movie at the @thecdnacademy Comedy & Drama Screen Awards alongside so many talented people!

So great to see friends old and new, and to celebrate all the winners and nominees. Canada has a hell of a lot of talent, and, in my opinion, some of the best comedy out there! 

Hair and makeup by moi, hair color by the fab @re_nato_v and dress found at @cultgaia 

Congrats to all on their nominations, wins, and for looking so fabulous! 🍁 

#canadianscreenawards #christmasmoviemagic
🇨🇦 

Special shout-out to the hosts for keeping things moving, particularly @realemmahunter  for lighting up that stage!

Alberta putting on a sun show. Tune in tonight to see my character make her grand entrance on @ridehallmarkchannel. ‘Grand’ might not be the word for it, actually. Maybe suspicious is better--can one make a suspicious entrance?

What a special cast - @nancytravisofficial @tskovbye1 @jakefoy55 @sara.alicia.garcia @beau_mirchoff 

Watch on @hallmarkchannel tonight or catch and stream after it’s out! There are lots of ways to watch.

🐎 🐎 🐎

From @polarized_movie: ‘As we celebrate Lesbian Visibility Week, it is important to recognize and appreciate the diversity within the lesbian community.

The film “Polarized” by @shamimsarif is a powerful exploration. Unexpected connection between two women from the same town, but very different worlds.’

It was a pleasure to play the character of ‘Lisa’ in Polarized as she discovers herself, alongside the talented @maxinedenis, whose character undergoes a similar journey.

Will forever remember those days in Winnipeg and the surrounding area with the incredible team - @shamimsarif, @maxinedenis, @hananfkattan, @julijetteinc, @tarasamuelofficial

🌈

🎬🎬🎬 

Here comes the… SEQUEL to 2021’s My Boss’s Wedding!!

Could not be more excited to reunite with this wonderful group of artists to create another fun, romantic movie for viewers to enjoy. 

We’re halfway through filming and let me tell you - it’s gonna be good one. 😘

🐎 so fun to have dropped in on a couple episodes of
@ridehallmarkchannel!

The season finale is tonight and it is a thing to behold. I wish I could’ve kept the wardrobe - cowboy hats are both a hoot and a holler to wear. 

Fingers crossed we get to see more of this wonderful cast and crew!!!

POLARIZED CANADIAN PREMIERE 🎉 
Clearly VERY excited to be able to share this with everyone! The film will premiere in THEATERS on June 23rd, with many screenings to follow. Check out the link in my stories (or highlights) or go to @polarized_movie to lock down some tickets!! Can’t wait to see you there, Wonder Woman!!
♥️ 

Also many thanks to @jesse_rath for editing this together for me & @jamieingall for filming and laughing at my struggles!!

Click through on my highlights for ticket info, or check out @polarized_movie and click link in-bio.

june, july, august, september

1. cloudy harbor in Toronto
2. the MAJESTY of somewhere in Utah
3. photos of my father circa late 1950s
4. a wonderful night; polarized at the Revue on Roncey
5. excellent reads - Nettle and Bone is my fav of the year so far
6. sweet boy in Wyoming
7. an Iowa storm we rushed into like fools
8. a very fun read
9. snapped while doing some serious thinking, yes that is a dragon
10. home

Thank you to all who tuned into ‘Our Christmas Wedding’, sequel to ‘My Boss’s Wedding’!! It was such a pleasure to reunite with the incredible and musically gifted @drewseeley, the effervescent @winnyclarke, the beautiful and generous @beekingsley and our awesome director @andrewcymek. 

December is fast approaching and if you haven’t checked it out, Our Christmas Wedding can be seen via Philo, DirectTV Stream, FuboTV and Sling! Hopefully I’ll be able to share some 🇨🇦 news soon. ✨

A throwback to this film @polarized_movie that was a huge part of the last few years of my life. So honored to still be receiving positive messages from those who watched and were moved by this story! 

It was a special group of people that brought this to life. Glad I got to be a part of it. Movies like this are more important now than ever… Lisa and Dalia found peace in each other. I wish the rest of the world would follow their lead. 

Xx
